headlines.description: Sandy Cohen III scored a career-high 36 points to lead Green Bay to a 96-90 victory against Oakland on Thursday night to snap a four-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cohen scores 36 points; Green Bay beats Oakland 96-90

headlines.description: Ako Adams hit a 3-pointer at the overtime buzzer to give Rice a 79-76 victory over Florida Atlantic in a Conference USA battle Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adams' buzzer-beating trey gives Rice 79-76 OT win over FAU

headlines.description: Jaylen Shaw scored 15 points and Tyrell Gumbs-Frater added four 3-pointers and 14 points to help Coastal Carolina defeat Little Rock 65-60 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coastal Carolina leads entire way in 65-60 victory

headlines.description: Kaelon Wilson had a career-high 23 points and Kevin Hervey added 21 as UT Arlington dominated the second half to even its Sun Belt Conference record, beating Georgia Southern 83-63 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson, Hervey lead UT Arlington to win over Ga. Southern

headlines.description: Broderick Robinson just missed a double-double, scoring 18 points and grabbing nine rebounds as UMKC won its fourth straight game, thumping UT Rio Grande Valley, 83-59 in a Western Athletic Conference battle Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UMKC wins 83-59, now tied with UT Rio Grande Valley in WAC

headlines.description: Bogdan Bliznyuk scored 27 points, 19 in the second half, and Eastern Washington beat Weber State with a 75-70 victory on Thursday night that ended the Wildcats' nine-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bliznyuk scores 27, Eastern Washington beats Weber St. 75-70

headlines.description: Frankie Ferrari turned in a double-double and San Francisco pulled into a tie with Pacific for the No. 4 seed into the West Coast Conference tournament by upsetting the Tigers, 84-74 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ferrari drives San Francisco past Pacific, 84-74, into 4th

headlines.description: Conner Toolson drained five from long range to score 22 points and Kenneth Ogbe added 14 as Utah Valley continued its hot streak to dominate Cal State Bakersfield 70-47 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah Valley continues hot streak, beating CSU Bakersfield

nowFeed.headline:
I followed Grayson Allen closely since his high school days. A fierce  competitor who gave it his all. He never had one issue on or off the court. I called Duke's game last year when Grayson Allen had his tripping incident. Tonight on senior night in a win over North Carolina I loved listening to Maria Taylor's post-game interview with Allen. 
What does Duke mean to you? 
" It means everything to me, it's my love and my passion. " Allen said. 
I call that growing up.
